#. <section class="sutta" id="sn4.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Tatiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Rule"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Māradhītusutta"
msgstr "25. Māra’s Daughters"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.273"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: abhāsitvā → bhāsitvā (s1-3)
#. VAR: appaṭibhāno → appaṭibhāṇo (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn4.25:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato santike imā nibbejanīyā gāthāyo abhāsitvā "
"tamhā ṭhānā apakkamma bhagavato avidūre pathaviyaṃ pallaṅkena nisīdi "
"tuṇhībhūto maṅkubhūto pattakkhandho adhomukho pajjhāyanto appaṭibhāno "
"kaṭṭhena bhūmiṃ vilikhanto."
msgstr ""
"And then Māra the Wicked, after reciting these verses of disillusionment in "
"the Buddha’s presence, left that place. He sat cross-legged on the ground "
"not far from the Buddha, silent, embarrassed, shoulders drooping, downcast, "
"depressed, with nothing to say, scratching the ground with a stick."

# Amending Arati to Rati, following the argument in Marcus Bingenheimer, Studies in Āgama Literature 4.5.
#. VAR: arati → aratī (s2, s3)
#. VAR: ragā → rāgā (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn4.25:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro yena māro pāpimā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsiṃsu:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra’s daughters Craving, Delight, and Lust went up to Māra the Wicked, "
"and addressed him in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.1"
msgid "“Kenāsi dummano tāta,"
msgstr "“Why so downhearted, dad?"

# I don’t want to read a gay subtext into this, but there’s totally a gay subtext. Mara’s fascination with the Buddha was more than professional; he was practically a stalker.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.2"
msgid "purisaṃ kaṃ nu socasi;"
msgstr "What man are you upset about?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.3"
msgid "Mayaṃ taṃ rāgapāsena,"
msgstr "We’ll catch him with the snare of lust,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.4"
msgid "āraññamiva kuñjaraṃ;"
msgstr "like an elephant in the wild."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.5"
msgid "Bandhitvā ānayissāma,"
msgstr "We’ll tie him up and bring him back—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:2.6"
msgid "vasago te bhavissatī”ti."
msgstr "he’ll fall under your sway!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:3.1"
msgid "“Arahaṃ sugato loke,"
msgstr "“In this world he is the perfected one, the Holy One."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:3.2"
msgid "na rāgena suvānayo;"
msgstr "He’s not easily seduced by lust."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:3.3"
msgid "Māradheyyaṃ atikkanto,"
msgstr "He has gone beyond Māra’s dominion;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:3.4"
msgid "tasmā socāmahaṃ bhusan”ti."
msgstr "that’s why I’m so upset.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.274"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
" upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra’s daughters Craving, Delight, and Lust went up to the Buddha, and "
"said to him:"

msgctxt "sn4.25:4.2"
msgid "“pāde te, samaṇa, paricāremā”ti."
msgstr "“We serve at your feet, ascetic.”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:4.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā na manasākāsi, yathā taṃ anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""
"But the Buddha ignored them, since he was freed with the supreme ending of "
"attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.125"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro ekamantaṃ apakkamma evaṃ "
"samacintesuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then Craving, Delight, and Lust withdrew to one side to think up a plan."

msgctxt "sn4.25:5.2"
msgid "“uccāvacā kho purisānaṃ adhippāyā."
msgstr "“Men have a diverse spectrum of tastes."

msgctxt "sn4.25:5.3"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ ekasataṃ ekasataṃ kumārivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmā”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t we each manifest in the form of a hundred young maidens?”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:5.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro ekasataṃ ekasataṃ "
"kumārivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"So that’s what they did. Then they went up to the Buddha and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn4.25:5.5"
msgid "“pāde te, samaṇa, paricāremā”ti."
msgstr "“We serve at your feet, ascetic.”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:5.6"
msgid "Tampi bhagavā na manasākāsi, yathā taṃ anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""
"But the Buddha still ignored them, since he was freed with the supreme "
"ending of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:6.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro ekamantaṃ apakkamma evaṃ "
"samacintesuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Then Craving, Delight, and Lust withdrew to one side to think up a plan."

msgctxt "sn4.25:6.2"
msgid "“uccāvacā kho purisānaṃ adhippāyā."
msgstr "“Men have a diverse spectrum of tastes."

msgctxt "sn4.25:6.3"
msgid "Yannūna mayaṃ ekasataṃ ekasataṃ avijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Why don’t we each manifest in the form of a hundred women who have never "
"given birth?”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:6.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro ekasataṃ ekasataṃ "
"avijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"So that’s what they did. Then they went up to the Buddha and said to him:"

msgctxt "sn4.25:6.5"
msgid "“pāde te, samaṇa, paricāremā”ti."
msgstr "“We serve at your feet, ascetic.”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:6.6"
msgid "Tampi bhagavā na manasākāsi, yathā taṃ anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""
"But the Buddha still ignored them, since he was freed with the supreme "
"ending of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr "Then Craving, Delight, and Lust …"

msgctxt "sn4.25:7.2"
msgid ""
"yannūna mayaṃ ekasataṃ ekasataṃ sakiṃ vijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:7.3"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:7.4"
msgid ""
"sakiṃ vijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"each manifested in the form of a hundred women who have given birth once …"

msgctxt "sn4.25:7.5"
msgid "“pāde te, samaṇa, paricāremā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:7.6"
msgid "Tampi bhagavā na manasākāsi, yathā taṃ anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.275"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.2"
msgid "yannūna mayaṃ ekasataṃ ekasataṃ duvijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.3"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.4"
msgid "duvijātavaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "women who have given birth twice …"

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.5"
msgid "yathā taṃ anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.6"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.7"
msgid "majjhimitthivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.8"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.9"
msgid "majjhimitthivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā … pe …"
msgstr "middle-aged women …"

msgctxt "sn4.25:8.10"
msgid "anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.2"
msgid "mahitthivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimmineyyāmāti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.3"
msgid "Atha kho taṇhā ca … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.4"
msgid "mahitthivaṇṇasataṃ abhinimminitvā yena bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "old women …"

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.5"
msgid "anuttare upadhisaṅkhaye vimutto."
msgstr ""
"But the Buddha still ignored them, since he was freed with the supreme "
"ending of attachments."

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro ekamantaṃ apakkamma "
"etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then Craving, Delight, and Lust withdrew to one side and said:"

msgctxt "sn4.25:9.7"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira no pitā avoca:"
msgstr "“What our father said is true:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:10.1"
msgid "‘Arahaṃ sugato loke,"
msgstr "‘In this world he is the perfected one, the Holy One."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:10.2"
msgid "na rāgena suvānayo;"
msgstr "He’s not easily seduced by lust."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:10.3"
msgid "Māradheyyaṃ atikkanto,"
msgstr "He has gone beyond Māra’s dominion;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:10.4"
msgid "tasmā socāmahaṃ bhusan’ti."
msgstr "that’s why I’m so upset.’"

# The final vā here is unwarranted, cp. similar passages at AN 11.6, AN 5.190, etc.
#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.126"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:11.1"
msgid ""
"Yañhi mayaṃ samaṇaṃ vā brāhmaṇaṃ vā avītarāgaṃ iminā upakkamena "
"upakkameyyāma hadayaṃ vāssa phaleyya, uṇhaṃ lohitaṃ vā mukhato uggaccheyya, "
"ummādaṃ vā pāpuṇeyya cittakkhepaṃ vā."
msgstr ""
"For if we had come on to any ascetic or brahmin like this who was not free "
"of lust, his heart would explode, or he’d spew hot blood from his mouth, or "
"he’d go mad and lose his mind."

msgctxt "sn4.25:11.2"
msgid "Seyyathā vā pana naḷo harito luto ussussati visussati milāyati;"
msgstr ""
"He’d dry up, wither away, and shrivel up like a green reed that was mowed "
"down.”"

msgctxt "sn4.25:11.3"
msgid "evameva ussusseyya visusseyya milāyeyyā”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.276"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:12.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;"
" upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra’s daughters Craving, Delight, and Lust went up to the Buddha, and "
"stood to one side."

msgctxt "sn4.25:12.2"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho taṇhā māradhītā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Māra’s daughter Craving addressed the Buddha in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:13.1"
msgid "“Sokāvatiṇṇo nu vanamhi jhāyasi,"
msgstr "“Are you overwhelmed by sorrow that you meditate in the forest?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:13.2"
msgid "Vittaṃ nu jīno uda patthayāno;"
msgstr "Have you lost a fortune, or do you long for one?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:13.3"
msgid "Āguṃ nu gāmasmimakāsi kiñci,"
msgstr "Or perhaps you’ve committed some crime in the village?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:13.4"
msgid "Kasmā janena na karosi sakkhiṃ;"
msgstr "Why don’t you get too close to people?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:13.5"
msgid "Sakkhī na sampajjati kenaci te”ti."
msgstr "And why does no-one get close to you?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:14.1"
msgid "“Atthassa pattiṃ hadayassa santiṃ,"
msgstr "“I’ve reached the goal, peace of heart."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:14.2"
msgid "Jetvāna senaṃ piyasātarūpaṃ;"
msgstr "Having conquered the army of the likable and pleasant,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Ekohaṃ → ekāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.25:14.3"
msgid "Ekohaṃ jhāyaṃ sukhamanubodhiṃ,"
msgstr "alone, practicing absorption, I awakened to bliss."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:14.4"
msgid "Tasmā janena na karomi sakkhiṃ;"
msgstr "That’s why I don’t get too close to people,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:14.5"
msgid "Sakkhī na sampajjati kenaci me”ti."
msgstr "and no-one gets too close to me.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
#. VAR: arati → aratī (s2, s3) | arati ca (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.25:15.1"
msgid "Atha kho arati māradhītā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra’s daughter Delight addressed the Buddha in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.277"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:16.1"
msgid "“Kathaṃvihārībahulodha bhikkhu,"
msgstr "“How does a mendicant who has crossed five floods"

# See BB’s note; the Skt texts here have present tense. Even before i realized this I couldn’t make sense of this pada and assumed there must be some such corruption. Note that the change could come about simply by dropping one “t”: Pañcoghatiṇṇo (t)atarīdha chaṭṭhaṃ. I translate assuming present tense is correct.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:16.2"
msgid "Pañcoghatiṇṇo atarīdha chaṭṭhaṃ;"
msgstr "usually meditate here while crossing the sixth?"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Kathaṃ jhāyiṃ → kathaṃ jhāyaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1-2) | kathajjhāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.25:16.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ jhāyiṃ bahulaṃ kāmasaññā,"
msgstr "How do they usually practice absorption so that sensual perceptions"

# aladdha here = pwned
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:16.4"
msgid "Paribāhirā honti aladdha yo tan”ti."
msgstr "are warded off and don’t get hold of them?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:17.1"
msgid "“Passaddhakāyo suvimuttacitto,"
msgstr "“With tranquil body and mind well freed,"

# asankharano is unusual in this context, and this is a guess. I suspect it means not living the holy life aspiring for rebirth in the deva realms.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:17.2"
msgid "Asaṅkharāno satimā anoko;"
msgstr "without making plans, mindful, homeless;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:17.3"
msgid "Aññāya dhammaṃ avitakkajhāyī,"
msgstr ""
"understanding the teaching, they practice absorption without placing the "
"mind;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:17.4"
msgid "Na kuppati na sarati na thino."
msgstr "they’re not shaking or drifting or rigid."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:18.1"
msgid "Evaṃvihārībahulodha bhikkhu,"
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant who has crossed five floods"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:18.2"
msgid "Pañcoghatiṇṇo atarīdha chaṭṭhaṃ;"
msgstr "usually meditates here while crossing the sixth."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:18.3"
msgid "Evaṃ jhāyiṃ bahulaṃ kāmasaññā,"
msgstr "That’s how they usually practice absorption so that sensual perceptions"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:18.4"
msgid "Paribāhirā honti aladdha yo tan”ti."
msgstr "are warded off and don’t get hold of them.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.127"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
#. VAR: ragā → rāgā (s1-3) | ragā ca (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.25:19.1"
msgid "Atha kho ragā māradhītā bhagavato santike gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then Māra’s daughter Lust addressed the Buddha in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.278"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:20.1"
msgid "“Acchejja taṇhaṃ gaṇasaṅghacārī,"
msgstr "“He lives with his community after cutting off craving,"

# See BB for tarissanti.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:20.2"
msgid "Addhā carissanti bahū ca saddhā;"
msgstr "and many of the faithful will cross over for sure."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:20.3"
msgid "Bahuṃ vatāyaṃ janataṃ anoko,"
msgstr "Alas, this homeless one will snatch many men away,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:20.4"
msgid "Acchejja nessati maccurājassa pāran”ti."
msgstr "and lead them past the King of Death!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:21.1"
msgid "“Nayanti ve mahāvīrā,"
msgstr "“The great heroes they lead"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:21.2"
msgid "saddhammena tathāgatā;"
msgstr "by means of the true teaching."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:21.3"
msgid "Dhammena nayamānānaṃ,"
msgstr "When the Realized Ones are leading by the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:21.4"
msgid "kā usūyā vijānatan”ti."
msgstr "how could anyone who knows be jealous?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:22.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho taṇhā ca arati ca ragā ca māradhītaro yena māro pāpimā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then Māra’s daughters Craving, Delight, and Lust went up to Māra the Wicked."

msgctxt "sn4.25:22.2"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho māro pāpimā taṇhañca aratiñca ragañca māradhītaro dūratova "
"āgacchantiyo."
msgstr "Māra the Wicked saw them coming off in the distance,"

msgctxt "sn4.25:22.3"
msgid "Disvāna gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "and addressed them in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:23.1"
msgid "“Bālā kumudanāḷehi,"
msgstr "“Fools! You drill into a mountain"

#. <br>
#. VAR: abhimatthatha → abhimanthatha (bj, pts2)
msgctxt "sn4.25:23.2"
msgid "pabbataṃ abhimatthatha;"
msgstr "with lotus stalks!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:23.3"
msgid "Giriṃ nakhena khanatha,"
msgstr "You dig up a hill with your nails!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:23.4"
msgid "ayo dantehi khādatha."
msgstr "You chew iron with your teeth!"

# I find this metaphor hard to understand. The verse bears some resemblance to SN 36.4, where the patala is said to be under the ocean. I assume it means you’re trying to swim with a rock on your head!
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.279"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
#. VAR: sirasūhacca → sirasi ūhacca (si) | sirasi ohacca (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.25:24.1"
msgid "Selaṃva sirasūhacca,"
msgstr "You seek a footing in the deeps, as it were,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:24.2"
msgid "pātāle gādhamesatha;"
msgstr "while lifting a rock with your head!"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:24.3"
msgid "Khāṇuṃva urasāsajja,"
msgstr "After attacking a stump with your breast, as it were,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:24.4"
msgid "nibbijjāpetha gotamā”ti."
msgstr "you leave Gotama disappointed.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:25.1"
msgid "“Daddallamānā āgañchuṃ,"
msgstr "“They came in their splendor—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:25.2"
msgid "taṇhā ca aratī ragā;"
msgstr "Craving, Delight, and Lust."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:25.3"
msgid "Tā tattha panudī satthā,"
msgstr "But the Teacher brushed them off right there,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:25.4"
msgid "tūlaṃ bhaṭṭhaṃva māluto”ti."
msgstr "like the breeze, a fallen tuft.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn4.25:25.5"
msgid "Tatiyo vaggo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "sn4.25:26.1"
msgid "Sambahulā samiddhi ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:26.2"
msgid "Godhikaṃ sattavassāni;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:26.3"
msgid "Dhītaraṃ desitaṃ buddha,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn4.25:26.4"
msgid "Seṭṭhena imaṃ mārapañcakanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn4.25:26.5"
msgid "Mārasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses with Māra are complete."
